comments: Conley (MIN) steps into Dinwiddie (BKN) around the screen and as a result, Dinwiddie brings his arm forward.  The contact between the two players is marginal.
Bridges (BKN) engages and disengages with Gobert (MIN) and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
Dinwiddie (BKN) initiates contact to Conley (MIN) when he controls the rebound that causes him to lose his balance.
Conley (MIN) maintains a legal guarding position while defending Dinwiddie (BKN) on the perimeter.
Finney-Smith (BKN) is already in Conley's (MIN) path and does not deliver contact.
Gobert (MIN) is in a legal guarding position when he contests Dinwiddie's (BKN) jump shot attempt and the marginal contact is created by Dinwiddie.
Dinwiddie (BKN) extends his leg during his jump shot attempt, but the contact is marginal.
Edwards (MIN) dribbles the ball off of Bridges' (BKN) leg and he does not intentionally kick the ball.
Dinwiddie (BKN) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Edwards (MIN) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Gobert (MIN) commits a take foul on Dinwiddie (BKN).

O'Neale (BKN) bring his arm forward and marginal contact occurs with Edwards' (MIN) face as he is able to come down with the rebound. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Bridges (BKN) moves alongside of Edwards' (MIN) path to the basket and legally contests the driving shot attempt.
McDaniels (MIN) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.
Anderson (MIN) commits a take foul on Bridges (BKN).
Anderson (MIN) brings his arm toward Dinwiddie's (BKN) shoulder and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
O'Neale (BKN) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Edwards's (MIN) arm.
Anderson (MIN) is moving alongside Dinwiddie's (BKN) path and marginal body contact occurs prior to Dinwiddie releasing the pass.
Dinwiddie (BKN) lowers his arms to contest the driving shot attempt by Edwards (MIN) and any contact is marginal.
Bridges (BKN) reaches in and initiates contact to Edwards's (MIN) front that affects his SQBR during the drive.
Dinwiddie (BKN) steps forwards towards Edwards (MIN) and absorbs the contact to the body.  Any arm contact is marginal during the pass.
Dinwiddie (BKN) legally contests Conley's (MIN) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
